rom other guilds on our raid who have there own Vox raids. This very much offended me and upset me. I noticed a Few from CoGF alliance with the Lore Guardians Tag. They have there own Rotation why is it that they can come on our raids. Isnt this a violation of KGC rules. This is just my thoughts. See you all Happy adventures in game<br>
<br>
 Mack225........ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhaemish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haemish</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>CoG Founder</span><br>  Posts: 566<br> <font color=#8E9173>(6/24/01 3:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=211.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.godwin.com/sd/haemish.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Guess on Dragon Raids</span><hr size=1> Actually, on Vox and Nagafen, guests are allowed because of the level restrictions on Vox and Naggy, according to the KGC rules. Since many of the larger, higher level guilds were having trouble getting enough people UNDER level 53, the restriction against guests were lifted. As for that particular raid, the SB was having a problem getting enough of the right classes (i.e. enchanters, damage casters and necros) without which a Vox run is suicide. So I asked reps from each guild in the Sacred Band alliance to ask their friends who were of these classes to come help. Thankfully they did, otherwise we  (the SB) would have had to pass. <br>
<br>
It's only on larger, higher level targets, such as Venril Sathir, the gods, the Kunark dragons and Trakanon/Zlandicar that guests aren't allowed by KGC rules. <br>
<br>
Haemish <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ueressiakallisti.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EressiaKallisti</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#8E9173>(6/25/01 7:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=211.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.twilite.org/~chrome/images/sigs/eresphoto.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Guess on Dragon Raids</span><hr size=1> What I'm wondering is: Why post about that here?  If you'd have come to any of the Illuminatus Officers (or any of the Officers in the Sacred Band), I'm sure everything would have been explained to you.<br>
<br>
Please, in the future, don't ever be too scared to ask questions.  I heard a Chinese proverb the other day that went something like this (I know this will be a slight misquote):<br>
<br>
&quot;He who asks a question is a fool for 5 minutes.  He who does not ask a question is a fool for a lifetime.&quot;<br>
<br>
All in all, I am glad that you did ask a question, but it concerns me that you didn't discuss this with one of your guild's own officers first.<br>
<br>
If you'd like to reveal who you are, I'd love to discuss any problems you may be having.  Also remember that other officers (with whom you may feel more comfortable) are there for you too. <p><img src="http://www.twilite.org/~chrome/images/sigs/eressig.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bcouncilofguilds.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kellory>Kellory</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Unguilded Sexless Drood</span><br>  Posts: 62<br> <font color=#8E9173>(6/26/01 10:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=211.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Guess on Dragon Raids</span><hr size=1> Hmmm...but what happens if all you do is question?  Doesnt that make me a fool for a lifetime too?  Or it just could be I am a fool.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Oh well, I'm sure this is news to no one.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I would say this probably is a good place for the question.  While I agree he probably should have gone through guild leadership, at the same time this is a question that tends to pop up a lot.  Not really surprisingly considering how messed up KGC can be sometimes.  After all, KGC is not held together by trust or friendship but rather more by mutual self interest.  The thing is this way at least more people who might also have been wondering the same thing but not willing to look silly by asking a question that everyone else obviously knew the answer to, now knows.  I'm sure Mack225 didnt mean any harm in posting his question here and it does reach (I hope) a larger audience.<br>
<br>
