<br>
First off Lag my intent with these discussions were to get all the disagreements and arguments out now before they happen again.  However, they were never meant to accuse anyone of doing something wrong on the previous raids.  If I actually said so (I dont think I did, but I'm not sure) or even implied such then you have my deepest apologies.  As for not saying things sooner, well thats because I dont think during a raid is the time to bring up anything that can cause trouble.  And nothing causes trouble faster than people complaining about loot, especially if one of them is a group leader.  Oringally I never had any intention of going on that Vox raid and only attended because either you or Flarren had posted that you might need help due to not enough people potentially showing up.  I came not for the loot, not even for the fun or experience, but because someone I trust and respect said they needed some help.  So bottom line I didnt complain or say anything.  Perhaps I should have sent a private tell, but keeping everything going was kind of hard on that raid.  And the second raid, well Vox kinda poped up suddenly and I felt ideology and idealism needed to take a back seat to reality and pragmatism.  And while the person leading the raid isnt perfect, they do deserve every benefit of the doubt and they deserve the respect of not arguing with them.  And so I dont.  If you think thats a mistake on my part well, perhaps it is.  But for now it's still my own personal belief.<br>
<br>
My first Vox raid was in January of 2001.  Does that give me any right to say anything?  Perhaps I havent been doing it as long, but I think 6 months qualifies me for some public opinions.<br>
<br>
As to the whole Valoran situation well a lot of people just dont like uber guilds and those that belong to them.  I think thats a silly attitude by they exist.  Also a lot of people probably havent been on raids you've lead and so they're just looking at your guild tag.  I'm sorry they exist and if I knew who they were they'd certainly get more than a small piece of my mind, but you'll always have idiots like that and I'm sorrry but thats a price you'll have to pay for being in a large guild.  For me, I just remember how many of Zellex's raids Valoran has joined in on and rolled on, not to mention that Vox raid only to find out that when I went on a Valoran DN raid I wasnt allowed to roll on the black marble that dropped.  Now I understand the whole quest gem for the guild thing and all that, but I was asked to come over there and help Valoran recover their corpses in there and stayed because they were short of healers and died several times.  True, I didnt come for the loot I came because a friend asked me to so it didnt bother me too much.  But it shows me how the larger guilds think.  As far as I'm concerned individual members of Valoran are great, some are friends (I hope I can still count you and flarren as 2) but the guild as a whole I could do without.  And there are many who dont even bother to seperate out individuals.  Those people are sadder and poorer for their attitude, but they do exist.<br>
<br>
As far as excluding you I agree with Haemish, I think its sad anyone would think of doing so.  The two of you have earned a place here with blood, sweat, and tears by running raids when no one else was able or willing to step up.  That alone earns you a place on any raid that the KGC rules say you can attend.  And yes, I have so stated and told Kommisar that straight out the last time he asked me before Naggy.  We may or may not agree on everything, but thats life.  Friendship is supposed to transcend things like that, not destroy them.  I think discussion and even arguments can be good and sometimes theaputic, but at the end of the day we all need to remember the while this is a game it's played by other people not just ourselves.<br>
<br>
I wanted these discussions to be about how best to solve loot problems and how best to run and work these raids.  Yes, I've wanted it done my way, but in the end if I want things my way I should get off my lazy ass and run the raid.  But seeing as how people are begining to take things the wrong way (not necessarily you Lag) and these threads dont seem to be doing anything more than stirring up animosity and causing poeple to take sides, perhaps its time to just lets these threads drop.  Let the raid leaders make their decisions and let them be final.  If we dont like it, run the raid ourselves next time.  Just my thoughts anyway.  Feel free to disagree after all, historiclly I've been wrong more often than I've been right.<br>
<br>
Kellory Silverstar<br>
Druid, 52, Edible<br>
